vention of competition.  Section 12(A) (2) provides guidance to the Commission as to the relevant factors it should take into account when making this determination. The Commission is required to consider factors relevant to competition including the chara
cteristics of the product itself, the market, the level of import competition in that market, the ease of entry in that market, the history of the collusion or co-ordination between firms in that market, whether there has been a history of failures, the ex
